pre-requisites:
1. eksctl installed
2. kubectl installed
3. awscli installed
4. awscli is configured
5. must have pem key with us
6. eks cluster created
7. eksctl version


Note: 
You canâ€™t create managed nodes in an AWS Region where you have AWS Outposts or AWS Wavelength enabled. You can create self-managed nodes instead.

Creating the node-group for the existing cluster :
command:

eksctl create nodegroup \
  --cluster my-eks-cluster \
  -- region us-east-1 \
  --name my-mng-ng \
  --node-ami-family ami-family \
  --node-type m5.large \
  --nodes 3 \
  --nodes-min 2 \
  --nodes-max 4 \
  --ssh-access \
  --ssh-public-key my-key 
  

  
